The paper discusses the political dimensions of adversarial machine learning attacks and defenses, which suggests that it could belong to the categories of computer security (cs.CR), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), cybernetics (cs.CY), and social and information networks (cs.SI). The focus on the potential risks to civil liberties and human rights also suggests that it could be more likely to belong to the categories of computer security and social and information networks.
